        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 3:17PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 317 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Greenhorn Mountain, or 36 miles southwest of
Pueblo, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Huerfano
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
